WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:03.437
Frank:
South Central Los Angeles.

00:03.471 --> 00:05.406
You hear those words,
and already,

00:05.439 --> 00:07.508
there's a story coming together
in your head.

00:07.541 --> 00:10.178
Like when people talk
about the Old West.

00:10.211 --> 00:13.047
You see two gunfighters
on a dusty street,

00:13.081 --> 00:15.549
but no one thinks about
how those fellas got there,

00:15.583 --> 00:17.518
why they're about to
pull the trigger,

00:17.551 --> 00:19.687
who else might catch one
when the bullets fly.

00:19.720 --> 00:21.755
Only way to know the real story

00:21.789 --> 00:25.193
is to put yourself
in their boots.

00:25.226 --> 00:26.394
Man: I'm saying, though,
Miss Kelly,

00:26.427 --> 00:28.796
you can't just listen to
all that soft-ass college rock.

00:28.829 --> 00:31.432
First of all,
watch your language, please,

00:31.465 --> 00:33.134
around these kids.

00:33.167 --> 00:35.069
Second of all,
I can listen to whatever I want.

00:35.103 --> 00:36.670
This is America.

00:36.704 --> 00:39.107
You've got to at least
listen to some Kendrick.

00:39.140 --> 00:41.242
He's got that hood thing
and that college vocabulary,

00:41.275 --> 00:42.343
you know what
I'm saying?

00:42.376 --> 00:44.612
All right.
I'll make you guys a deal.

00:44.645 --> 00:46.814
I'll give Kendrick a try
as long as you all promise

00:46.847 --> 00:49.250
to come to one class this week
at the Center, okay?

00:49.283 --> 00:51.252
Learn some of that
college vocabulary.

00:51.285 --> 00:52.686
[ Tires squealing ]

00:52.720 --> 00:53.721
Man: What?

01:02.696 --> 01:03.731
[ Screams ]

01:03.764 --> 01:05.699
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:11.739 --> 01:15.143
[ Dog barking ]

01:15.176 --> 01:17.211
[ Siren wailing ]

01:25.186 --> 01:26.086
[ Clears throat ]

01:26.120 --> 01:27.721
Look, counselor,
I know you're a busy man,

01:27.755 --> 01:29.757
but we're dealing
with a case

01:29.790 --> 01:31.492
possibly related
to Water Street,

01:31.525 --> 01:34.228
so any light you may be able
to shed would --

01:39.267 --> 01:40.568
What was your name again,
officer?

01:40.601 --> 01:41.835
Detective -- Craig.

01:41.869 --> 01:44.838
Oh, excuse me --
Detective Craig.

01:44.872 --> 01:48.209
Okay, here's a hypothetical,
Detective Craig.

01:48.242 --> 01:49.877
Say a cop
walks into your office

01:49.910 --> 01:51.745
and asks about
a 10-year-old case --

01:51.779 --> 01:53.614
a case in which
your client was charged

01:53.647 --> 01:55.216
with murdering
a police officer

01:55.249 --> 01:56.817
on the evidence
of a planted firearm.

01:56.850 --> 01:58.386
Allegedly planted.

01:58.419 --> 02:00.288
Oh.
That's the spirit.

02:00.321 --> 02:03.224
Only, this detective shares
the last name

02:03.257 --> 02:05.726
with the arresting officer
in said case --

02:05.759 --> 02:07.127
Billy Craig.

02:08.796 --> 02:10.731
Well, hypothetically,
if I were the lawyer,

02:10.764 --> 02:13.734
I would see it as an opportunity
to find out the truth.

02:13.767 --> 02:16.670
You're not here working
a case related to
Water Street, are you?

02:18.706 --> 02:20.374
You're here as a son.

02:20.408 --> 02:22.843
A son with, obviously,
grave doubts about his father.

02:24.312 --> 02:26.647
And my job isn't
about the truth.

02:26.680 --> 02:29.783
It's about representing
my client -- Delvon Lincoln.

02:29.817 --> 02:31.819
[ Gunfire, sirens wailing ]

02:31.852 --> 02:32.853
Teflon.

02:34.522 --> 02:36.524
He claimed he was in the employ
of a dirty cop,

02:36.557 --> 02:38.326
which is the reason --
so he claimed --

02:38.359 --> 02:40.294
that no charges against him
ever stuck.

02:40.328 --> 02:41.829
Hence, the name Teflon.

02:41.862 --> 02:43.231
Okay, then,
why shoot a cop?

02:43.264 --> 02:44.532
Why bite the hand
that feeds him?

02:44.565 --> 02:46.667
Now, that is
an excellent question.

02:46.700 --> 02:49.303
Why would a drug dealer with a
permanent "Get out of jail" card

02:49.337 --> 02:51.572
want to shoot
a police officer?

02:51.605 --> 02:53.841
Seems to me Teflon made
a hell of a fall guy.

02:55.276 --> 02:56.677
That's not
who my father was.

02:58.446 --> 02:59.780
Do you have any idea
why I'm comfortable

02:59.813 --> 03:01.415
putting aside
attorney/client privilege

03:01.449 --> 03:03.317
to even talk to you
about this matter?

03:04.585 --> 03:06.920
Because there is
no attorney/client
privilege any longer.

03:06.954 --> 03:09.357
It died with Teflon.

03:09.390 --> 03:11.692
90 minutes after being remanded
into Twin Towers,

03:11.725 --> 03:13.527
43 stab wounds.

03:13.561 --> 03:15.563
[ Screaming ]

03:15.596 --> 03:17.365
His mattress
looked like a sponge.

03:17.398 --> 03:18.866
Unsolved, of course.

03:21.402 --> 03:23.003
Sounds like a hit.

03:23.036 --> 03:25.739
I believe they call that
"tying up a loose end."

03:27.341 --> 03:29.610
[ Cellphone rings ]

03:32.546 --> 03:34.382
[ Cellphone beeps ]

03:34.415 --> 03:35.716
Who did it?

03:35.749 --> 03:37.451
On the inside?

03:37.485 --> 03:39.287
I heard Mexican Mafia.

03:39.320 --> 03:40.421
Mexican Mafia?

03:40.454 --> 03:41.855
Why them?
Who were they working for?

03:41.889 --> 03:43.757
[ Scoffs ] I have no idea,
Detective Craig,

03:43.791 --> 03:46.594
but I suspect
that was the point.

03:46.627 --> 03:48.729
There'd be nobody left
to ask,

03:48.762 --> 03:50.364
and there wasn't --

03:50.398 --> 03:52.600
until you stepped into
my office.

03:54.635 --> 03:56.537
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:05.479 --> 04:06.914
Welcome, detectives.

04:06.947 --> 04:08.749
Today was not
a good day.

04:08.782 --> 04:09.883
All this
for a drive-by?

04:09.917 --> 04:11.852
The victims are two males,
black --

04:11.885 --> 04:14.388
apparently,
West Compton Mob-affiliated --

04:14.422 --> 04:16.557
and a girl -- Kelly Price,
not from the neighborhood.

04:16.590 --> 04:18.926
Where from, then?
What was she doing here?

04:18.959 --> 04:21.829
Well, she worked here while she
was getting her master's degree.

04:21.862 --> 04:24.365
Raised in Baldwin Hills,
went on to UCLA,

04:24.398 --> 04:25.899
graduated
summa cum laude.

04:25.933 --> 04:28.302
She was outside on the steps
talking to a group of kids,

04:28.336 --> 04:31.539
when a car pulls up --
one driver, one shooter.

04:31.572 --> 04:32.973
No one got a good look
at them.

04:33.006 --> 04:35.509
Frank: Well, that explains
the dog-and-pony show.

04:35.543 --> 04:36.644
Take her
out of the picture

04:36.677 --> 04:38.078
and this never even
makes the news.

04:38.111 --> 04:40.614
The other two,
you said West Compton Mob?

04:40.648 --> 04:42.783
That's right. They've got
gang cards on file.

04:42.816 --> 04:45.786
Nothing major,
but they're definitely banging.

04:45.819 --> 04:48.422
West Compton Mob still feuding
with the Avalon Royals?

04:48.456 --> 04:50.491
[ Scoffs ] Like the Hatfields
and the McCoys.

04:50.524 --> 04:52.393
Nice to know
some things never change.

04:52.426 --> 04:54.027
Shall we pay a visit,
trainee?

04:54.061 --> 04:55.563
In a second.

05:01.068 --> 05:02.770
[ Feedback ]

05:02.803 --> 05:04.472
In moments like these,

05:04.505 --> 05:07.808
I believe it's important
to reflect on who we are.

05:07.841 --> 05:10.544
What's up, guys?
My name's Kyle.

05:10.578 --> 05:12.079
You police?

05:12.112 --> 05:13.881
I'm a detective.

05:13.914 --> 05:15.716
You good police
or bad police?

05:17.551 --> 05:19.086
I try to be a good one.

05:19.119 --> 05:21.555
Yeah,
but you're not always.

05:21.589 --> 05:23.090
I'm always trying.

05:23.123 --> 05:24.792
Just like Kelly
was always trying to be

05:24.825 --> 05:26.860
the best teacher
she could be, right?

05:28.462 --> 05:32.433
How we want our children
to see us -- to see themselves.

05:32.466 --> 05:36.404
You know the best way
to be a good policeman?

05:36.437 --> 05:37.371
I don't know.

05:37.405 --> 05:39.573
Maybe try not to shoot
so many black folks?

05:42.109 --> 05:45.112
That...
and talk to people.

05:45.145 --> 05:50.984
Because at times like these,
it's easy to lose your way.

05:51.018 --> 05:53.120
You hear anyone talk
about the shooting,

05:53.153 --> 05:54.688
who they thought it was?

05:58.426 --> 06:01.895
...and resources
to delivering justice.

06:01.929 --> 06:04.465
I just threw up
in my mouth.

06:04.498 --> 06:06.434
[ Applause ]

06:06.467 --> 06:08.869
Stirring oration,
Deputy Chief Lockhart.

06:08.902 --> 06:09.803
Cram it.

06:09.837 --> 06:13.574
Joy. What you said
meant a lot to all of us.

06:14.642 --> 06:16.577
Frank,
this is Todd Barber.

06:16.610 --> 06:19.647
He sponsors this
and many other community centers

06:19.680 --> 06:21.148
around Los Angeles.

06:21.181 --> 06:22.483
That's very generous.

06:22.516 --> 06:24.618
Not really.
I grew up with nothing.

06:24.652 --> 06:27.488
Not in a neighborhood like this,
but kids deserve a place to go.

06:27.521 --> 06:29.189
Doesn't matter
what neighborhood.

06:29.222 --> 06:31.759
Detective Rourke is
running point on this case.

06:31.792 --> 06:32.626
I am?

06:33.694 --> 06:34.462
I am.

06:34.495 --> 06:35.463
I didn't know Kelly
personally,

06:35.496 --> 06:38.699
but I know what she meant
to the people here.

06:38.732 --> 06:40.568
The response from
your department's been great.

06:40.601 --> 06:42.169
You know, we have
our own security team.

06:42.202 --> 06:43.937
They'd be more than happy
to pitch in

06:43.971 --> 06:45.473
if you think
they could help.

06:45.506 --> 06:46.507
In fact...

06:46.540 --> 06:47.441
Paul?

06:47.475 --> 06:49.076
Detective Rourke,
this is Paul DiNardo --

06:49.109 --> 06:51.044
spent 20 years
with the sheriff's department,

06:51.078 --> 06:52.212
now my head of security.

06:52.245 --> 06:54.648
I'll be straight with you,
fellas -- when I'm out hunting,

06:54.682 --> 06:55.816
I don't like
to catch scent

06:55.849 --> 06:57.551
of anyone else
stomping through the woods.

06:57.585 --> 06:58.486
Know what I mean?

06:58.519 --> 07:00.521
Not here to step
on any toes, Detective.

07:00.554 --> 07:02.556
Luckily,
we're not dancing.

07:02.590 --> 07:05.793
Gentlemen, Detective,
Deputy Chief.

07:05.826 --> 07:07.928
Sean: My mom says
never talk to police --

07:07.961 --> 07:09.730
about anything.

07:09.763 --> 07:12.600
They'll twist you up
and put a case on you.

07:12.633 --> 07:14.134
I'm not here
to twist you up.

07:14.167 --> 07:16.570
I just want the men
who did this -- the bad guys.

07:18.972 --> 07:20.941
You know who
the Avalon Royals are, right?

07:20.974 --> 07:21.942
You see them?

07:21.975 --> 07:24.011
Were they in the car?

07:24.044 --> 07:25.913
How about
any of your friends?

07:27.815 --> 07:29.449
Somebody saw something.

07:36.690 --> 07:38.992
You're not a snitch.
I respect that.

07:44.565 --> 07:45.666
I'll see you around.

07:45.699 --> 07:47.167
[ Joe Budden's "Serious" plays ]

07:47.200 --> 07:49.537
[ Rapping ] * Man,
y'all done gone and did it *

07:49.570 --> 07:50.971
* Well, come on with it

07:51.004 --> 07:52.640
* The fifth got a kick,
but won't slip *

07:52.673 --> 07:53.574
* I rubber-gripped it

07:53.607 --> 07:55.175
* Wrap you in them sheets
on Christmas *

07:55.208 --> 07:56.544
* I'm double-gifted

07:56.577 --> 07:57.511
* Double-barrel shotty

07:57.545 --> 07:58.779
* You double-jointed
when you flippin' *

07:58.812 --> 08:02.115
* Ask about your boy, they'll
tell you I'm not the fella *

08:06.554 --> 08:07.855
Ignore the first runner.

08:07.888 --> 08:09.089
He's just holding
the dope.

08:11.825 --> 08:12.960
There's your shot caller.

08:18.799 --> 08:20.868
-Five-0!
-Yo, cops, man!

08:20.901 --> 08:22.636
Should've worn
your Nikes.

08:28.075 --> 08:29.209
[ Grunts ]

08:31.612 --> 08:33.013
[ Gun cocks ]
Don't!

08:37.618 --> 08:39.787
You're probably used to shooting
unarmed black men, huh?

08:41.755 --> 08:44.291
Not so easy
knowing I'll shoot back.

08:47.595 --> 08:49.697
Is that your big-yard stare,
hardass?

08:49.730 --> 08:50.664
It might scare
the little old lady

08:50.698 --> 08:52.265
at the corner store,
but I'm not impressed.

08:52.299 --> 08:54.768
You wouldn't last 15 minutes
in Afghanistan.

08:54.802 --> 08:56.036
You're all talk, rookie.

08:57.070 --> 08:59.172
I don't fear
the oppressors --

08:59.206 --> 09:00.808
or their house slaves.

09:00.841 --> 09:02.042
Take off that badge
and gun.

09:02.075 --> 09:03.911
I'll show you how we get down
out here, boy.

09:05.212 --> 09:07.981
Give it a rest. You're not gonna
goad my partner into --

09:08.015 --> 09:10.618
It's been a slow morning,
anyway.

09:10.651 --> 09:12.185
50 bucks
on my trainee.

09:12.219 --> 09:13.887
Got you covered
on that one.

09:26.399 --> 09:27.601
Whoo!

09:27.635 --> 09:29.803
Oh, man!

09:29.837 --> 09:32.673
Your old man's smiling down
from Heaven right now.

09:34.341 --> 09:36.710
You want to cry
police brutality now?

09:36.744 --> 09:40.080
Yeah. I seen how you get down
out here, homey.

09:40.113 --> 09:43.016
Dope-slinging and drive-bys
do not a revolution make.

09:45.252 --> 09:47.688
How many brothers
you put in the ground?

09:47.721 --> 09:48.822
How many kids
you orphan, huh?

09:48.856 --> 09:50.090
How many kids you have?

09:51.424 --> 09:53.226
You got
a lot of anger, bruh.

09:53.260 --> 09:54.928
I'm not a therapist
or anything,

09:54.962 --> 09:57.765
but you can't carry
all that anger with you.

09:57.798 --> 10:00.033
You could get cancer
or something.

10:00.067 --> 10:02.102
You shot a civilian,
and her only crime

10:02.135 --> 10:04.838
was standing next to a bunch
of gangsters from West Compton.

10:06.039 --> 10:08.709
Everybody knows you guys
been beefing with West Compton

10:08.742 --> 10:10.410
since the dawn of man.

10:10.443 --> 10:13.413
You think I'd be
out on the corner after
pulling a drive-by?

10:13.446 --> 10:15.215
You need to check
your assumptions, bruh.

10:15.248 --> 10:17.985
[ Hip-hop music playing ]

10:18.018 --> 10:20.921
Looks like we're not
the only ones making
assumptions this morning.

10:20.954 --> 10:23.223
[ Music stops ]

10:24.291 --> 10:25.058
You're trespassing.

10:25.092 --> 10:26.660
We just come
to take what's ours.

10:26.694 --> 10:28.061
What's that,
little homey?

10:28.095 --> 10:29.096
Your life, bruh.

10:33.366 --> 10:34.735
Guys! Guys!

10:34.768 --> 10:36.003
Hey! Guys, come on.

10:36.036 --> 10:38.806
Why get ourselves into some
"High Noon" type situation here

10:38.839 --> 10:41.308
when we could just put down
some cardboard and settle this

10:41.341 --> 10:43.343
with an old-fashioned
breakdance competition?

10:45.078 --> 10:46.079
Dice?

10:48.048 --> 10:49.016
"Yo' mama" jokes?

10:49.049 --> 10:51.218
[ Scoffs ]
Man, you crazy.

10:51.251 --> 10:52.953
You're here
for the same reason we are --

10:52.986 --> 10:54.788
the drive-by
that killed Kelly Price.

10:57.825 --> 10:59.960
Man, you know we won't hit you
in front of the Center, right?

10:59.993 --> 11:02.429
Why?
What about the Center?

11:05.899 --> 11:08.268
Community Center's
supposed to be off-limits --

11:08.301 --> 11:09.837
a neutral zone.

11:09.870 --> 11:12.840
Violate that,
that's a capital crime.

11:12.873 --> 11:15.075
But y'all pigs don't got to
worry about it. We got this.

11:16.476 --> 11:17.845
That's not how it works.

11:17.878 --> 11:18.912
Yeah?
Then how does it work?

11:18.946 --> 11:21.381
Let me tell you
how it's gonna work.

11:21.414 --> 11:23.784
You give us 24 hours
to figure out who it is.

11:23.817 --> 11:26.920
24 hours,
we bring you a name.

11:26.954 --> 11:29.156
We don't, then you can turn
the neighborhood into Fallujah,

11:29.189 --> 11:30.390
for all I care.

11:33.360 --> 11:34.795
24 hours.

11:34.828 --> 11:36.329
And then
the bodies start dropping.

11:37.464 --> 11:39.299
And ISIS ain't got nothing
on us.

11:47.975 --> 11:49.943
**

11:49.977 --> 11:51.945
[ Siren wails,
police radio chatter ]

12:09.662 --> 12:10.197
[ Engine revving ]

12:14.334 --> 12:15.202
You just cut a deal

12:15.235 --> 12:17.504
for a 24-hour truce
in South Central.

12:17.537 --> 12:19.206
Time's running out.

12:19.239 --> 12:21.374
We have no next moves,
and you're playing games.

12:21.408 --> 12:22.375
Helps me think.

12:22.409 --> 12:24.277
We should have put bracelets
on all these dudes.

12:24.311 --> 12:25.979
Are you really buying
that the Avalon Royals

12:26.013 --> 12:27.147
weren't involved
in the shooting?

12:27.180 --> 12:29.449
You never worked the South End,
like me and your dad did.

12:29.482 --> 12:31.251
There's a rhythm
to these things.

12:31.284 --> 12:33.486
Those guys knew
we'd come calling.

12:33.520 --> 12:35.088
They didn't lie low.

12:35.122 --> 12:36.523
Tells me
they're not involved --

12:36.556 --> 12:37.858
not directly.

12:37.891 --> 12:39.259
So, then,
we have nothing.

12:40.427 --> 12:42.562
This one's gotten
under your skin, huh?

12:42.595 --> 12:43.797
That's good.

12:43.831 --> 12:45.165
But you can't force it.

12:45.198 --> 12:46.099
Not gonna get anywhere

12:46.133 --> 12:47.868
running around South Central
busting heads.

12:47.901 --> 12:48.902
They're used to it.

12:50.037 --> 12:51.538
Have faith, trainee.

12:51.571 --> 12:53.506
Drive-bys
are like mule deer --

12:53.540 --> 12:55.442
they follow
a well-worn path.

12:55.475 --> 12:58.411
In the next 12 hours, the car
from the drive-by will show up.

12:58.445 --> 12:59.546
Trust me.

12:59.579 --> 13:02.015
Then we'll have
a trail to follow.

13:02.049 --> 13:03.550
Doesn't give us
a lot of time.

13:08.455 --> 13:11.091
[ Dog barking in distance ]

13:11.124 --> 13:13.126
You want a cup?

13:13.160 --> 13:15.863
I'll take a beer.

13:15.896 --> 13:17.430
That's not gonna help.

13:19.466 --> 13:22.870
Where are you, son?

13:22.903 --> 13:23.736
Talk to me.

13:26.206 --> 13:28.942
You heard about this girl --
Kelly Price?

13:28.976 --> 13:31.311
The one who was shot.

13:31.344 --> 13:33.580
I'm not sure what it is
about this one,

13:33.613 --> 13:36.917
but I feel
connected somehow.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.887
Maybe you see this girl
the way you see yourself.

13:39.920 --> 13:41.288
What do you mean?

13:41.321 --> 13:45.192
Doing her part in a neighborhood
she felt connected to

13:45.225 --> 13:47.560
but not one
she fully understood.

13:47.594 --> 13:49.362
I do understand.

13:49.396 --> 13:50.931
I'm on the outside
looking in.

13:50.964 --> 13:53.600
She...became a part of it.

13:53.633 --> 13:56.403
Black man with a badge.

13:56.436 --> 13:58.571
Your father struggled
with it, too.

13:58.605 --> 14:02.142
Did Dad ever mention
the Water Street case to you?

14:03.643 --> 14:05.212
It was
one of his last cases --

14:05.245 --> 14:08.348
just a few months
before...

14:08.381 --> 14:11.184
He wasn't himself
the last few months.

14:11.218 --> 14:13.853
Not himself enough
to plant a gun on a guy?

14:15.188 --> 14:16.256
Your father?

14:16.289 --> 14:17.490
That's not all.

14:17.524 --> 14:21.394
This guy,
he was killed in prison --

14:21.428 --> 14:23.230
maybe to keep him quiet.

14:23.263 --> 14:26.033
Is this really
about your father's legacy

14:26.066 --> 14:27.600
or is this
about you justifying

14:27.634 --> 14:29.502
the work that you do
with Frank Rourke?

14:31.004 --> 14:32.639
Because
I've seen a change.

14:32.672 --> 14:36.643
And what really worries me is,
I'm not sure that you have.

14:36.676 --> 14:39.646
Solving your father's murder
isn't why you became a cop.

14:39.679 --> 14:43.250
And I think this girl, Kelly,
reminds you of that.

14:43.283 --> 14:45.252
But you can be
all these things, Kyle --

14:45.285 --> 14:48.055
Billy's son,
Frank's partner.

14:48.088 --> 14:52.926
But the most important thing is,
baby, don't lose yourself.

15:02.002 --> 15:03.103
Nothing
in witness statements.

15:03.136 --> 15:06.139
Exactly what you'd expect
with a gang-related shooting.

15:06.173 --> 15:07.674
People are worried
about their own kids.

15:07.707 --> 15:08.408
Vicious cycle.

15:08.441 --> 15:09.376
And the surveillance
footage

15:09.409 --> 15:11.678
gave us no clear angle
on the shooters?
Nope.

15:11.711 --> 15:14.681
What about the West Compton guys
who got killed at the scene?

15:14.714 --> 15:16.716
Well, they've got gang cards
on file --

15:16.749 --> 15:18.285
low-level dealers.

15:18.318 --> 15:19.719
Managed
to piss somebody off.

15:19.752 --> 15:22.022
This one doesn't
feel right, man.

15:22.055 --> 15:23.556
How's it
supposed to feel?

15:23.590 --> 15:25.658
Someone punches a hole
in the fabric of the universe,

15:25.692 --> 15:27.660
it lingers, you know?

15:27.694 --> 15:30.998
Just out of professional
curiosity, are you high?

15:31.031 --> 15:33.200
I know what you mean, but no.
This is really him.

15:33.233 --> 15:36.003
This girl Kelly, she was
all positive charge, right?

15:36.036 --> 15:38.038
Surrounded by light,
and something --

15:38.071 --> 15:40.007
something upset
the natural order.

15:40.040 --> 15:41.975
Wait.

15:42.009 --> 15:43.710
You might actually
be onto something.

15:43.743 --> 15:45.245
Well,
don't act too surprised.

15:45.278 --> 15:46.579
[ Scoffs ]
Not about the hippie garbage,

15:46.613 --> 15:48.348
but something's definitely wrong
with this shooting.

15:48.381 --> 15:50.017
Check out
the spray pattern.

15:53.320 --> 15:56.056
The shooter brought the muzzle
back around.

15:56.089 --> 15:57.324
Oh, I see it --

15:57.357 --> 15:59.092
left to right
and then back again.

15:59.126 --> 16:01.228
And the concentration
of firepower is there.

16:02.229 --> 16:04.164
Right where
Kelly was sitting.

16:04.197 --> 16:06.299
She wasn't in the wrong place
at the wrong time.

16:07.367 --> 16:09.002
Kelly was the target.

16:09.036 --> 16:11.038
**

16:14.241 --> 16:16.143
[ Radio chatter ]

16:18.378 --> 16:20.780
Dispatcher:
All units be advised --
vehicle in drive-by recovered.

16:20.813 --> 16:23.450
One suspect down,
two in custody.

16:23.483 --> 16:26.519
Frank:
What'd I tell you, trainee?
Just like mule deer.

16:26.553 --> 16:28.055
You're right
about the car.

16:28.088 --> 16:30.023
Make and model line up
with witness statements.

16:30.057 --> 16:32.092
Plates look like they're burned
beyond recognition.

16:32.125 --> 16:34.127
Doesn't matter.
It's stolen.

16:34.161 --> 16:36.463
Suspects jacked it
to pull the drive-by,

16:36.496 --> 16:38.765
then torched it to cover up
any physical evidence.

16:38.798 --> 16:40.267
Pretty standard stuff,

16:40.300 --> 16:43.570
except this one looks like
arson interruptus.

16:52.412 --> 16:53.513
Raw Dogg?

16:53.546 --> 16:55.448
And ISIS ain't got nothing
on us.

16:55.482 --> 16:56.616
Gentlemen.

17:00.387 --> 17:02.722
DiNardo?
What the hell's he doing here?

17:02.755 --> 17:05.425
Rent-a-cop says they were here
on an investigation,

17:05.458 --> 17:08.195
sniffing around the 'hood for
the guys who shot Kelly Price.

17:09.396 --> 17:12.265
Catches Raw Dogg here
torching the suspect vehicle.

17:12.299 --> 17:15.668
Raw Dogg pulls on him,
Paul Blart comes out on top.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.104
He's licensed
to carry --

17:17.137 --> 17:19.139
says he fired
in defense of his own life.

17:19.172 --> 17:20.073
No witnesses.

17:20.107 --> 17:22.209
So, supposedly,
Raw Dogg shot his own guys

17:22.242 --> 17:23.810
because of some kind
of internal beef?

17:23.843 --> 17:25.278
Wouldn't be
the first time.

17:25.312 --> 17:26.579
But Kelly
was the target.

17:27.680 --> 17:30.683
Maybe that girl wasn't
as innocent as she seemed.

17:30.717 --> 17:31.818
I don't buy it.

17:31.851 --> 17:34.154
Trainee's
got a point.

17:34.187 --> 17:36.423
Yesterday, Raw Dogg
was ready to start a war

17:36.456 --> 17:38.291
to avenge his homeys.

17:38.325 --> 17:40.360
We're missing something.

17:40.393 --> 17:43.696
DiNardo agreed to come down
to RHD and give a statement.

17:46.233 --> 17:47.467
Is that right?

17:52.472 --> 17:55.342
Hey, Paul.
Appreciate you coming down.

17:55.375 --> 17:57.777
Boss said you used to be
with the sheriff's.

17:57.810 --> 17:59.479
This must
bring it all back, huh?

17:59.512 --> 18:02.249
The hum of fluorescence,
the rustling of paper...

18:02.282 --> 18:03.883
the pinching of asses
in pantsuits.

18:03.916 --> 18:05.152
[ Laughs ]

18:05.185 --> 18:06.586
Coffee used to
be better.

18:06.619 --> 18:08.421
A drop of whiskey
will fix that right up.

18:08.455 --> 18:10.457
Oh, I remember.

18:10.490 --> 18:14.261
Listen --
one cop to another --

18:14.294 --> 18:16.596
this was a righteous shooting,
Frank.

18:16.629 --> 18:19.166
Brother, I hear you.

18:19.199 --> 18:20.433
Trust me --
I don't care.

18:20.467 --> 18:22.335
I saw
Raw Dogg's rap sheet.

18:22.369 --> 18:27.374
Like we used to say --
NHI, no humans involved.

18:30.377 --> 18:31.878
Nowadays, it's easier
to shoot someone

18:31.911 --> 18:33.480
if you're not police,
huh?

18:33.513 --> 18:36.749
No I.A. investigation,
trial by media.

18:36.783 --> 18:38.218
Damn right.

18:38.251 --> 18:41.754
One thing bugs me, though --
one cop to another.

18:41.788 --> 18:44.557
You got there first,
which means...

18:44.591 --> 18:46.659
you held out on me,
DiNardo.

18:49.662 --> 18:51.864
Mr. Barber felt
it was his responsibility

18:51.898 --> 18:53.200
to make things right.

18:53.233 --> 18:54.467
His responsibility?

18:54.501 --> 18:56.436
How's that?

18:56.469 --> 18:58.738
This girl was shot
on his property, right?

18:58.771 --> 19:00.673
That translates
to legal liability.

19:00.707 --> 19:03.410
He was anxious to deliver
justice to the girl's parents

19:03.443 --> 19:06.379
in order to prove to them
that he cared.

19:06.413 --> 19:08.415
You still haven't given me
a straight answer

19:08.448 --> 19:10.817
as to how you just happened
to be Johnny-on-the-spot.

19:12.952 --> 19:15.222
Because I was able to do
what you can't --

19:15.255 --> 19:17.624
what we never could --
spread some money around.

19:17.657 --> 19:20.159
Goes a lot further
than just asking questions.

19:23.696 --> 19:24.664
Who told you?

19:24.697 --> 19:26.499
[ Scoffs ] No.

19:26.533 --> 19:28.568
Even I don't give up
my sources, Detective.

19:29.902 --> 19:33.440
Look, I wanted to get the job
done right, done quick --

19:33.473 --> 19:34.807
for Kelly, all right?

19:34.841 --> 19:38.478
And I'm not the least bit
ashamed of how it turned out.

19:38.511 --> 19:39.779
You said it yourself --
you got to answer

19:39.812 --> 19:43.316
to Internal Affairs
and the jackals in the media.

19:43.350 --> 19:45.618
I just have to answer
to my own conscience.

19:45.652 --> 19:46.953
And Mr. Barber.

19:52.859 --> 19:53.626
What did he say?

19:53.660 --> 19:55.895
Claims he paid
for the information.

19:55.928 --> 19:57.664
Won't say who.

19:57.697 --> 19:59.399
At this point,
it doesn't matter who.

19:59.432 --> 20:01.501
Come on. What do we know
about this guy or his boss?

20:01.534 --> 20:02.502
Barber?

20:02.535 --> 20:04.704
Guy's got
a clean record, Kyle.

20:04.737 --> 20:06.906
Said he was a developer.
Humor him.

20:10.377 --> 20:11.978
Okay.
Started with strip malls.

20:12.011 --> 20:14.013
Apparently,
those weren't ugly enough,

20:14.046 --> 20:16.316
so he moved on
to housing developments.

20:16.349 --> 20:18.918
Best known for
the Aqua Mesa planned community.

20:18.951 --> 20:20.787
He live out there?
Yeah.

20:20.820 --> 20:22.555
So dude takes a strong interest
in South Central

20:22.589 --> 20:23.823
but lives as far away
as someone can get

20:23.856 --> 20:25.258
without leaving
the county.

20:25.292 --> 20:28.861
Would you rather him not help
rehab these community centers?

20:28.895 --> 20:31.864
Look, Kyle,
the preliminary ballistics

20:31.898 --> 20:33.633
line up just like
we thought they would.

20:33.666 --> 20:35.968
That is the weapon
that killed Kelly Price,

20:36.002 --> 20:38.271
on the ground,
lying next to Raw Dogg,

20:38.305 --> 20:39.906
with his prints
all over it.

20:39.939 --> 20:42.442
Now, none of us are thrilled
that DiNardo found him first,

20:42.475 --> 20:45.512
but sometimes
the bear eats you.

20:45.545 --> 20:48.348
So, Raw Dogg's the shooter.
Okay, but why?

20:48.381 --> 20:49.582
Why would he
target Kelly?

20:49.616 --> 20:52.018
Why would he put his own crew
in the line of fire to get her?

20:52.051 --> 20:53.886
How am I the only one who cares
why this girl died?

20:55.021 --> 20:56.356
And here comes the Joy.

20:56.389 --> 20:57.990
Lockhart:
Detectives, I need briefing

20:58.024 --> 21:00.593
so I can get this out
in front of the press.

21:00.627 --> 21:01.994
We could use
some more time.

21:03.330 --> 21:04.697
I'm confused.

21:04.731 --> 21:07.767
Do we or do we not have the
shooter and the murder weapon?

21:07.800 --> 21:10.670
Well, as it just so happens,
my distinguished trainee here

21:10.703 --> 21:11.904
was attempting to engage

21:11.938 --> 21:14.774
in some honest-to-goodness
detective work.

21:14.807 --> 21:16.776
What else is there
to solve?

21:16.809 --> 21:17.710
There's no motive.

21:17.744 --> 21:20.380
This isn't a court of law,
Detective Craig.

21:20.413 --> 21:22.449
We didn't need
to prove motive --

21:22.482 --> 21:24.451
just that Raw Dogg
was the shooter.

21:24.484 --> 21:25.685
Which we've done.

21:26.886 --> 21:28.588
We should be talking
to his boss.

21:28.621 --> 21:30.022
I already have.

21:30.056 --> 21:33.660
And I let Mr. Barber know
that we were less than pleased

21:33.693 --> 21:35.862
about his people's involvement
in the case.

21:35.895 --> 21:37.897
But there's much more
at stake here.

21:37.930 --> 21:40.600
We have a community
that needs healing

21:40.633 --> 21:43.603
and a public that needs to know
that we're effective.

21:43.636 --> 21:46.038
You will not pursue this
any further.

21:47.540 --> 21:48.975
Do you understand?

21:49.008 --> 21:51.478
As far as the department
is concerned,

21:51.511 --> 21:54.013
this investigation
is closed.

21:57.717 --> 22:00.520
Barber called her.

22:00.553 --> 22:03.790
10th floor must have some kind
of Bat Phone for rich people.

22:03.823 --> 22:05.625
The Bat Phone was
for a rich guy.

22:05.658 --> 22:06.793
That's right!

22:08.595 --> 22:10.029
I'm going out there.

22:10.062 --> 22:11.531
"Out there," trainee?

22:11.564 --> 22:12.899
That's way past Reseda.

22:12.932 --> 22:15.568
The sun'll be down soon.

22:15.602 --> 22:17.970
I hear tell
there are vampires out that way.

22:18.004 --> 22:18.971
Oh, God.

22:19.005 --> 22:20.940
What?
You don't like Tom Petty?

22:22.609 --> 22:24.577
You're not going anywhere,
Detective.

22:24.611 --> 22:25.745
You can't give me orders.

22:25.778 --> 22:27.614
I'm not under
your chain of command.
I'm under his.

22:29.148 --> 22:32.419
So, boss, the question is,
am I going out there alone...

22:33.620 --> 22:35.087
...or are you coming
with me?

22:35.121 --> 22:40.493
**

22:40.527 --> 22:44.063
**

22:44.096 --> 22:46.733
* Well, you worked all day

22:46.766 --> 22:49.636
Look at these houses --
no soul.

22:49.669 --> 22:50.537
[ Sighs ]

22:50.570 --> 22:53.005
Like rows of big,
stucco gravestones.

22:53.039 --> 22:55.742
Used to be horse country
and citrus groves out here.

22:55.775 --> 22:57.577
Ranchers sold their land,

22:57.610 --> 23:00.580
traded in their ponies
for jet skis.

23:00.613 --> 23:04.150
Groves got paved over
with asphalt and sod.

23:04.183 --> 23:07.053
What's the matter, trainee?
Suburbs got you down?

23:07.086 --> 23:10.056
You're even more stoic
than usual.

23:10.089 --> 23:13.125
You see someone like
Kelly Price, and you think,

23:13.159 --> 23:16.195
"There's so much more
I could be doing."

23:16.228 --> 23:18.898
She's the last person who should
be dying on the sidewalk.

23:18.931 --> 23:21.100
Nobody should be dying
on the sidewalk.

23:21.133 --> 23:24.537
Not Kelly Price,
not your old man.

23:25.872 --> 23:29.642
Truth is,
no one gets to choose.

23:29.676 --> 23:32.512
I went to see Jack Rawls
the other day.

23:32.545 --> 23:33.713
Know him?
Know him?

23:33.746 --> 23:35.715
Shaved his father
on his wedding day.

23:35.748 --> 23:36.783
'Course I know him.

23:36.816 --> 23:38.885
No one works harder
against the public interest

23:38.918 --> 23:40.787
than Jack Rawls, esquire.

23:40.820 --> 23:41.888
I don't know.

23:41.921 --> 23:44.791
He kind of reminded me of you --
like he got the joke.

23:46.025 --> 23:47.894
I won't be insulted
in my own car, trainee.

23:47.927 --> 23:50.763
It was your case that sent me
there -- Water Street?

23:50.797 --> 23:52.532
He represented
Delvon Lincoln --

23:52.565 --> 23:54.534
you know, Teflon.

23:54.567 --> 23:55.868
Is that right?

23:55.902 --> 23:57.704
Seemed to think
that Delvon Lincoln's death

23:57.737 --> 23:58.905
was some kind
of conspiracy,

23:58.938 --> 24:02.208
that he worked for dirty cops
who wanted to keep him quiet.

24:03.710 --> 24:05.077
Permanently.

24:05.111 --> 24:08.214
Somebody ordered a hit
on Teflon.

24:08.247 --> 24:10.249
[ Tires screech ]

24:10.282 --> 24:12.685
There something
you want to ask me?

24:12.719 --> 24:14.120
Was it you?

24:14.153 --> 24:15.488
And my dad?

24:17.557 --> 24:18.558
No.

24:19.859 --> 24:20.993
Then who was it?

24:29.001 --> 24:30.803
Go meet the neighbors.

24:36.809 --> 24:38.645
It's all your trucks.

24:38.678 --> 24:40.580
Every day, they clog the way
out of town.

24:40.613 --> 24:42.849
I'm waiting
at that freeway ramp meter

24:42.882 --> 24:44.984
10, 15 minutes
some mornings.

24:45.017 --> 24:46.252
What I don't
understand is,

24:46.285 --> 24:47.987
where in the hell
are they going?

24:48.020 --> 24:50.189
You're sending all those trucks
to the city.

24:50.222 --> 24:53.726
Meanwhile, we still don't have
the community pool center

24:53.760 --> 24:57.564
or those roads and houses
you promised for Phase 4 and 5.

24:57.597 --> 24:58.731
I understand
your impatience.

24:58.765 --> 24:59.766
[ Scoffs ]
Oh, really?

24:59.799 --> 25:02.835
But I give you my word
that Phase 4 and Phase 5

25:02.869 --> 25:04.136
and the community
pool center

25:04.170 --> 25:06.072
will all be finished
by the end of the year.

25:06.105 --> 25:07.073
[ Crowd murmuring ]

25:07.106 --> 25:09.275
Every Thursday evening --
Friday is trash day,

25:09.308 --> 25:12.044
so we have Manuela
put out the cans on Thursday.

25:12.078 --> 25:14.246
They come out of the shadows
like clockwork

25:14.280 --> 25:15.982
with little lights
on their cap

25:16.015 --> 25:17.984
and great big bags,
like gypsies.

25:18.017 --> 25:20.286
So far, they only seem
to want the trash,

25:20.319 --> 25:21.888
but what happens
when that's not enough?

25:21.921 --> 25:23.756
What then?

25:23.790 --> 25:26.025
Thanks, as always,
Mrs. Cheney.

25:26.058 --> 25:27.627
Protecting your recyclables

25:27.660 --> 25:30.129
is something the community
takes very seriously.

25:30.162 --> 25:31.731
If there are
no more concerns?

25:31.764 --> 25:33.165
Evening, folks.

25:33.199 --> 25:35.301
Detective Frank Rourke
of the LAPD,

25:35.334 --> 25:38.304
and this is my trainee,
Detective Kyle Craig.

25:38.337 --> 25:40.640
Mr. Barber invited us here
to remind you

25:40.673 --> 25:43.610
that Aqua Mesa leads the county
in prescription-drug abuse

25:43.643 --> 25:45.177
and damn fine pornography.

25:45.211 --> 25:47.747
So keep a friendly eye on
your neighbor, and remember --

25:47.780 --> 25:51.183
if you see something,
say something.

25:51.217 --> 25:53.185
[ Crowd murmuring ]

26:01.260 --> 26:03.362
Well, I got to hand it to you,
Detective Rourke --

26:03.395 --> 26:06.265
That's gonna go down as one of
the most colorful HOA meetings

26:06.298 --> 26:08.200
in Aqua Mesa history.

26:08.234 --> 26:09.636
This place
has history?

26:10.770 --> 26:12.672
What exactly can I do
for you two gentlemen?

26:12.705 --> 26:15.074
Well, we were hoping you could
help us understand something.

26:16.175 --> 26:17.343
I'll sure as heck try.

26:17.376 --> 26:19.345
Why was
Kelly Price murdered?

26:19.378 --> 26:21.848
You know, I wish I had an answer
for you, detectives, but --

26:21.881 --> 26:23.082
You were eager enough
to send him out

26:23.115 --> 26:25.251
and shoot the man
responsible for it.

26:25.284 --> 26:28.921
Makes it look an awful lot
like you didn't want us
getting to him first.

26:28.955 --> 26:31.223
You're damn right
I wanted to get there first.

26:31.257 --> 26:32.659
Lawyers told me I had to.

26:32.692 --> 26:34.761
Do you have any idea
what kind of liability

26:34.794 --> 26:36.328
I was exposed to
on this whole thing?

26:36.362 --> 26:38.364
You withheld evidence
and went after the shooters

26:38.397 --> 26:39.999
to avoid getting sued?

26:41.400 --> 26:43.970
I grew up in Bakersfield --
poor as dirt.

26:44.003 --> 26:46.338
And now I got everybody here
looking to me for answers.

26:46.372 --> 26:48.841
Not to mention the folks
down at the Community Center.

26:48.875 --> 26:51.210
I got a lot to protect,
so excuse me

26:51.243 --> 26:54.046
if I took care of that scumbag
before you got the chance,

26:54.080 --> 26:55.314
but I'm not sorry.

26:57.917 --> 26:59.085
Gentlemen.

27:10.196 --> 27:12.131
Still doesn't
feel right.

27:12.164 --> 27:13.199
[ Sighs ]

27:13.232 --> 27:16.235
Further proof that nothing good
ends in Aqua Mesa.

27:25.011 --> 27:27.413
It's the trucks.

27:27.446 --> 27:28.815
Keep talking.

27:28.848 --> 27:31.083
Like that guy
from the HOA meeting said --

27:31.117 --> 27:32.685
all these trucks
moving supplies,

27:32.719 --> 27:34.787
but they're behind
on construction

27:34.821 --> 27:36.723
in the man's
own development?

27:36.756 --> 27:39.458
It sure as hell
ain't headed to South Central.

27:39.491 --> 27:42.361
Todd Barber's a lot of things,
but he ain't that charitable.

27:42.394 --> 27:43.896
So what's he hiding?

27:43.930 --> 27:46.232
Everybody in his tax bracket's
hiding something.

27:46.265 --> 27:47.233
I'm not concerned
with everybody.

27:47.266 --> 27:50.102
I'm concerned with
why Kelly Price had to die.

27:50.136 --> 27:53.005
And our answers
are here -- somewhere.

27:55.474 --> 27:56.909
Tell me
you don't feel it.

28:00.112 --> 28:01.480
All right, trainee.

28:01.513 --> 28:03.049
Let's wait around
till the sun goes down

28:03.082 --> 28:03.916
and then have ourselves

28:03.950 --> 28:06.452
an old-fashioned
warrantless look-around.

28:08.888 --> 28:11.223
**

28:28.240 --> 28:29.742
Working late, huh?

28:29.776 --> 28:31.878
What would
Ms. Cheney say?

28:37.183 --> 28:39.151
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:39.185 --> 28:40.719
**

29:14.220 --> 29:16.155
[ Machinery whirring ]

29:26.065 --> 29:28.234
Well,
what do we have here?

29:28.267 --> 29:29.969
Cocaine.

29:30.002 --> 29:32.071
This goes way beyond
tax evasion.

29:33.339 --> 29:35.307
No wonder
they're up so late.

29:36.475 --> 29:38.310
Don't take a deep breath
unless you want to find out

29:38.344 --> 29:40.512
what it was like to be alive
during the '80s.

29:40.546 --> 29:41.914
Right.

29:41.948 --> 29:43.315
It's time to crash
the party.

29:51.123 --> 29:52.491
Ever been snow-globed?

29:54.560 --> 29:56.028
[ Gun cocks ]
Easy.

29:56.062 --> 29:57.529
[ Coughing ]

29:57.563 --> 29:59.465
Bet you want
to talk now, huh?

30:01.067 --> 30:02.068
Man #1: Freeze!
Man #2: Drop it!

30:02.101 --> 30:03.302
Hands up!

30:03.335 --> 30:04.336
Drop the guns!

30:07.039 --> 30:08.207
Whoa! Whoa!

30:09.308 --> 30:11.477
This is a flagrant
safety violation.

30:15.047 --> 30:16.983
You gentlemen
aren't wearing hard hats.

30:18.384 --> 30:19.385
And trust me...

30:21.253 --> 30:22.454
...accidents do happen.

30:22.488 --> 30:27.559
**

30:27.593 --> 30:28.995
So, this is why
Kelly Price died?

30:29.028 --> 30:29.996
Drugs?

30:30.029 --> 30:32.064
Kelly had a keen eye.

30:32.098 --> 30:34.600
She noticed some things
I wish she hadn't.

30:34.633 --> 30:35.601
[ Splash ]

30:35.634 --> 30:37.103
People depend on me.

30:39.038 --> 30:40.907
But Kelly just couldn't see
the bigger picture.

30:40.940 --> 30:42.274
Bigger picture, huh?

30:42.308 --> 30:43.609
I think I see it.

30:43.642 --> 30:45.878
You're overextended
at Aqua Mesa.

30:45.912 --> 30:47.446
So you got into bed
with the drug cartels

30:47.479 --> 30:48.881
and came up with
the bright idea

30:48.915 --> 30:51.450
of pressing cocaine
into drywall.

30:51.483 --> 30:54.486
Easy to transport
across state lines,

30:54.520 --> 30:56.155
break down, and distribute.

30:56.188 --> 30:58.357
Then you build
a few community centers,

30:58.390 --> 31:00.459
go into business
with the local gangs.

31:00.492 --> 31:02.394
Now you got yourself
a distribution network

31:02.428 --> 31:05.965
far away from your own
precious neighborhood.

31:05.998 --> 31:07.934
And then
Kelly Price happened.

31:07.967 --> 31:09.168
She probably came to you,

31:09.201 --> 31:10.970
expecting you didn't know
about it.

31:12.939 --> 31:15.241
And you made the decision
to take her life

31:15.274 --> 31:16.976
so you can save your own.

31:17.009 --> 31:19.145
DiNardo took care
of the rest.

31:19.178 --> 31:22.648
Stole a car, made Kelly's murder
look like a drive-by.

31:22.681 --> 31:26.285
He'd seen enough of them
when he was a cop.

31:26.318 --> 31:29.155
And Raw Dogg made
an easy fall guy.

31:29.188 --> 31:31.657
He caught you trying to torch
the car, and you kill him, too.

31:31.690 --> 31:33.125
I did the city a favor.

31:33.159 --> 31:35.161
Yeah?
What about Kelly Price?

31:36.228 --> 31:38.297
Her heart was always
in the right place.

31:38.330 --> 31:41.033
That's why I'm gonna put her
name on the Community Center.

31:43.335 --> 31:45.137
[ Clanking ]

31:49.475 --> 31:51.610
I can't memorialize you
the same way,

31:51.643 --> 31:55.147
but to me...

31:55.181 --> 31:58.017
this will always be
Frank Rourke's Dead End.

31:58.050 --> 32:00.919
[ Hip-hop music plays ]

32:06.725 --> 32:08.394
[ Music stops ]

32:11.998 --> 32:13.365
Gentlemen.

32:13.399 --> 32:15.134
Our meeting was
supposed to be tomorrow.

32:15.167 --> 32:16.702
We got
a schedule conflict.

32:18.337 --> 32:21.207
Well, as you can see,
I'm handling some business here.

32:21.240 --> 32:22.441
Oh, don't mind us.

32:22.474 --> 32:23.675
We can wait.

32:23.709 --> 32:25.177
You stupid?

32:26.412 --> 32:29.215
Making cops disappear is just
gonna bring down more heat.

32:29.248 --> 32:30.416
Then we all suffer.

32:30.449 --> 32:32.084
It's bad enough
the girl caught one.

32:34.386 --> 32:36.055
I told you --

32:36.088 --> 32:37.556
I found
the man responsible,

32:37.589 --> 32:39.125
and he's been dealt with
accordingly.

32:39.158 --> 32:40.459
Once these cops
are in cement,

32:40.492 --> 32:42.161
we're back in business,
as usual.

32:42.194 --> 32:43.462
You're being played!

32:43.495 --> 32:45.597
He's the one
who had Kelly shot.

32:45.631 --> 32:48.067
What's he talking about?

32:48.100 --> 32:49.201
Nothing.

32:49.235 --> 32:50.436
He's not talking
about anything.

32:50.469 --> 32:52.071
He's trying to save
his own skin.

32:52.104 --> 32:53.305
Frank: Think about it.

32:53.339 --> 32:55.374
Those gangsters weren't
the target. Kelly was.

32:55.407 --> 32:57.643
She was sharp -- she figured out
your little operation

32:57.676 --> 32:59.711
at the Community Center,
and she died for it.

32:59.745 --> 33:01.647
For your dope --
for nothing!

33:02.714 --> 33:05.417
That money in your pocket
has Kelly's blood on it.

33:05.451 --> 33:06.752
This true?

33:06.785 --> 33:08.220
[ Sighs ]

33:08.254 --> 33:09.421
Even if it was,

33:09.455 --> 33:11.590
you know the price
of doing business, homey.

33:16.262 --> 33:18.030
[ Gun cocks ]
I'm not your homey!

33:18.064 --> 33:19.231
[ Guns cocking ]

33:19.265 --> 33:20.999
Easy, fellas.

33:33.512 --> 33:34.646
Bang!

33:34.680 --> 33:36.548
* Bang, bang,
another body drop *

33:36.582 --> 33:38.317
* You can't stop the head nod

33:38.350 --> 33:41.287
* Shoot 'em up, bang, bang,
another body drop *

33:41.320 --> 33:42.688
* You can't stop the gunshots

33:42.721 --> 33:45.057
* I'll hit your block up,
you better lock up *

33:45.091 --> 33:47.393
* ...the gang...
don't stop *

33:47.426 --> 33:49.395
* Come back
in form of an assassin *

33:49.428 --> 33:51.397
* 300 yards
with the infrared action *

33:51.430 --> 33:53.499
* True pistoleer,
black Doc Holliday *

33:53.532 --> 33:56.268
* ...raider
of the modern day, hunh *

33:56.302 --> 33:59.105
* Shoot 'em up, bang, bang,
another body drop *

33:59.138 --> 34:00.672
* You can't stop the head nod

34:00.706 --> 34:03.509
* Shoot 'em up, bang, bang,
another body drop *

34:03.542 --> 34:05.577
* You can't stop the gunshots

34:12.718 --> 34:14.186
Going somewhere?

34:35.307 --> 34:36.708
[ Gunfire in distance ]

34:50.889 --> 34:52.824
[ Saw buzzing ]

35:14.213 --> 35:15.614
[ Groans ]

35:17.783 --> 35:19.685
NHI.

35:19.718 --> 35:22.388
No human involved.

35:39.538 --> 35:41.540
You bring enough violence
into this world...

35:43.942 --> 35:45.711
...it will
follow you home.

35:47.879 --> 35:49.381
Frank: Kyle!

35:49.415 --> 35:51.350
Is he worth it?

35:51.383 --> 35:53.519
That's what
you got to ask yourself.

35:53.552 --> 35:55.254
Will he be worth it
tomorrow?

35:56.488 --> 35:58.290
You good police
or bad police?

35:59.825 --> 36:01.560
[ Panting ]

36:16.675 --> 36:17.843
Barber: You idiots.

36:17.876 --> 36:19.578
In this town,
you don't build what I have

36:19.611 --> 36:22.348
without making friends
in some high places.

36:22.381 --> 36:24.416
I got insurance measures,
you know.

36:24.450 --> 36:26.352
So you can go ahead
and arrest me.

36:26.385 --> 36:27.686
See if it sticks.

36:27.719 --> 36:28.554
[ Grunts ]

36:29.888 --> 36:31.657
The only friends in high places
you're gonna have

36:31.690 --> 36:34.293
is the guy on the top bunk
in your cell in Chino.

36:34.326 --> 36:36.328
I bet he's
a real good listener.

36:37.496 --> 36:40.632
Do you know the story
of Saul from Tarsus?

36:40.666 --> 36:42.568
He was in a gang
called the Pharisees,

36:42.601 --> 36:44.270
until God hit him
with a bolt of lightning

36:44.303 --> 36:45.737
on the road to Damascus.

36:45.771 --> 36:47.606
Well, this is
your Damascus, Cuddy.

36:49.875 --> 36:51.910
You're the new head of security
at the Community Center.

36:51.943 --> 36:54.513
That means no dope,
no drive-bys,

36:54.546 --> 36:56.448
and let all the other sets
know of it.

36:56.482 --> 36:58.850
Anything pops off
within a mile of that place...

36:59.951 --> 37:02.688
I'm not God in this story,
Cuddy. I'm the lightning.

37:03.922 --> 37:05.457
And if I have to
strike you down again,

37:05.491 --> 37:07.593
I swear on my father
you'll never get up.

37:16.802 --> 37:17.803
Frank: Let's go.

37:18.937 --> 37:19.771
Hold up.

37:21.039 --> 37:24.376
If it's cool with you, I'd like
to make a citizen's arrest.

37:24.410 --> 37:25.611
Huh?

37:28.347 --> 37:29.615
Heartwarming
to see a young man

37:29.648 --> 37:31.450
take an interest
in his community.

37:34.453 --> 37:35.587
Wait a minute.

37:35.621 --> 37:37.255
We gonna see
what sticks.

37:48.534 --> 37:49.635
Alive.

37:51.937 --> 37:53.372
Alive.

37:56.642 --> 37:57.876
Come on, guys.

37:57.909 --> 37:59.811
Guys, w-we can work
something out.

37:59.845 --> 38:01.880
Come on. You want a house?
You can take your pick.

38:01.913 --> 38:04.883
Cuddy:
Nah, homey. This neighborhood's
creepy as hell.

38:24.936 --> 38:26.838
Good morning,
Detective Craig.

38:26.872 --> 38:28.740
I was hoping
you could shed some light

38:28.774 --> 38:30.509
on yesterday's events.

38:30.542 --> 38:32.444
Well, I'm just as shocked
as you are, ma'am.

38:32.478 --> 38:34.813
But now the community
can heal -- like you said.

38:34.846 --> 38:38.450
One injustice
does not excuse another.

38:38.484 --> 38:39.951
I don't know
what you mean.

38:39.985 --> 38:42.854
So you're telling me you and
Frank had nothing to do with it.

38:42.888 --> 38:44.590
Nothing to do
with what?

38:45.591 --> 38:46.992
Todd Barber was found

38:47.025 --> 38:50.396
in a very compromised position
last night.

38:50.429 --> 38:53.031
Someone clearly wanted
to make a statement.

38:53.064 --> 38:56.101
Seems to me the man pissed off
a lot of dangerous people.

38:56.134 --> 38:57.503
He's lucky to be alive.

38:57.536 --> 38:59.104
Indeed.

39:00.939 --> 39:04.610
I know that you went to see
Jack Rawls the other day.

39:04.643 --> 39:05.844
You had me followed?

39:05.877 --> 39:07.846
You forget who I am.

39:07.879 --> 39:10.115
I don't need
to have you followed, Kyle.

39:10.148 --> 39:12.651
People tell me things.

39:12.684 --> 39:16.655
So, is there anything
you would like to tell me?

39:18.790 --> 39:22.060
Whatever Frank and my father did
to put Teflon away,

39:22.093 --> 39:23.629
you signed off on that.

39:25.431 --> 39:27.065
So, what else?

39:27.098 --> 39:29.401
Did you approve what happened
to him on the inside?

39:32.904 --> 39:35.073
[ Chuckles ]

39:35.106 --> 39:37.142
Yeah.

39:37.175 --> 39:39.110
That's the answer
I expected.

39:41.179 --> 39:43.114
And there is something
I'd like to tell you.

39:44.683 --> 39:47.152
My eyes are open.

39:47.185 --> 39:50.088
I'm seeing the choices
you're making, Kyle --

39:50.121 --> 39:51.723
clear as day.

39:51.757 --> 39:54.460
And if you keep going down
this road,

39:54.493 --> 39:56.495
you'll be on your own.

39:59.698 --> 40:02.468
* Driving through the fog
with my high beams *

40:02.501 --> 40:04.536
* Putting on my Visine

40:04.570 --> 40:06.905
* Let me tell you
just what I seen *

40:06.938 --> 40:08.807
* Angels fallin' from the sky

40:08.840 --> 40:11.209
* I just hope
that they can take me *

40:11.242 --> 40:13.712
* Back to where
the pearly gates be *

40:13.745 --> 40:15.581
* And I been counting down
the days *

40:15.614 --> 40:18.183
* Because I know
we gotta die soon *

40:18.216 --> 40:20.819
* That just means
I get to fly soon *

40:20.852 --> 40:23.489
* And I know
I'm not the only one out here *

40:23.522 --> 40:25.557
* That's not afraid

40:25.591 --> 40:27.092
Solving
your father's murder

40:27.125 --> 40:30.061
isn't the only reason
that you became a cop.

40:30.095 --> 40:32.831
This girl, Kelly,
reminds you of that.

40:32.864 --> 40:34.766
* With every step
and every breath *

40:34.800 --> 40:37.202
* Know that I been livin'
by you *

40:37.235 --> 40:39.705
* Lord, just tell me,
what should I do? *

40:39.738 --> 40:41.540
* And I been counting down
the days *

40:41.573 --> 40:43.942
* 'Cause pretty soon,
this will be all gone *

40:43.975 --> 40:46.645
* And you're the one
that I'ma call on *

40:46.678 --> 40:48.514
* And that's how I know
I'll be free *

40:48.547 --> 40:51.683
* And won't be locked
inside a cage *

40:51.717 --> 40:52.818
* All right, all right

40:52.851 --> 40:54.686
* And now
I'm finally on my way *

40:54.720 --> 40:55.821
Hey, Sean?
Yeah?

40:55.854 --> 40:56.922
Come give me a hand.

40:58.256 --> 41:00.258
You know, it's tradition
to plant a tree

41:00.291 --> 41:01.627
for someone you've lost.

41:03.128 --> 41:04.863
I planted one for my dad.

41:08.600 --> 41:11.102
And we can plant this one
for Kelly.

41:11.136 --> 41:13.004
Thanks, man.

41:13.038 --> 41:15.707
* We can't help but shine

41:16.975 --> 41:19.511
Billy: Tearing stuff down --
that's easy.

41:19.545 --> 41:21.713
Building up --
that's hard.

41:21.747 --> 41:24.616
We try to leave this world a
little better than we found it.

41:24.650 --> 41:26.217
Remember that.

41:26.251 --> 41:29.588
* I can't help but shine

41:29.621 --> 41:33.124
* I still can't help but shine

41:33.158 --> 41:36.261
* I can't help but shine

41:36.294 --> 41:39.731
* We can't help but shine

41:39.765 --> 41:41.767
* I can't help but...
